column4: <content>Write to MAJZELS-WEBSTER, P. Bruegel II: Peasant Banquet, (copy after Vienna), P. Bruegel II,  ""Wedding Dance"" signed & dated 1622, advertised by John Mitchell, 250 Old Burlington Street, in Burl. Mag. March 1958, repr. p. VII. The Wedding Dance connected with the Johnson picture. The Banquet important because from P.B.II copy one can see that the third foot actually belongs to the man who hands the porridge to the bride.</content>
